ok... this feels like a super basic question, but here goes.  I'm trying to write an if statement to prevent a value from being outputted if it is not defined in a HUBDB field, but I'm not able to get it to work.  Wondering if any of you folks could help me out.

```                {{if row.location.lat is defined }}
                &lt;p&gt;The latitude is: {{ row.location.lat }}&lt;/p&gt;
                {{else}}
                &lt;!--do nothing--&gt;
                {{endif}} ```
